      <resourceName>Oslo-Bergen tagger</resourceName>
      <description>The Oslo-Bergen tagger is a robust morphological and syntactic tagger developed at the University of Oslo and at Uni Computing in Bergen over several years. The tagger consists of three main modules: a preprocessor with multitagger and compound analyser, a grammar module for morphological and syntactic disambiguation (Constraint Grammar) and a statistical module that removes the last of the remaining morphological ambiguity (only for Bokmål)</description>
